# Chantal's chicken parmigiana

## Serves 4

- 4 chicken breast halves, skinned and boned
- 3 eggs
- 1 Tbsp dry mustard
- 1 1/4 cup bread crumbs
- 1/4 cup grated parmesan cheese
- tsp oregano
- 4 Tbsp vegetable oil
- 4 Tbsp butter or margarine
- 1 cup tomato sauce
- 3/4 cup shredded mozzarella cheese

## Instructions

Pound chicken breasts very thin

Beat together the eggs and mustard

Combine bread crumbs, parmesan and oregano and lay out on a plate

Dip chicken in egg mixture, then coat both sides with the crumbs

Brown half the chicken on both sides over medium low heat in half the oil and butter. Repeat with the other half of the chicken and oil

Place browned chicken in single layer in a greased casserole dish

Spoon tomato sausce over chicken and sprinkle with mozzarella and a bit more parmesan

Bake at 350^o F for 20-25 minutes

Serve with spagetti or linguini noodles

Bask in the compliments
